BFN 

  [Text] The Federal government has reassured the 
international community of the safety of the Nigerian airports. 
The minister of transport and aviation, Mr. Ebenezer Babatope, 
gave the assurance at a seminar. 
  Mr. Babatope said the government had taken necessary 
precautions to ensure adequate security at the airports, 
pointing out that security standards outlined by the 
International Civil Aviation Organization had been complied 
with. The minister said the arrangement had been finalized for 
the signing of bilateral air service agreements with Poland, 
South Africa, and some countries in the former Soviet Union. 

